results.name: Decimal expansion of the inscribed sphere radius in a regular dodecahedron with unit edge.
comment: Equals phi^2/(2*xi), where phi is the golden ratio (A001622, 2*cos(Pi/5)) and xi is its associate (A182007, 2*sin(Pi/5)).
link: Stanislav Sykora, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2000
